<cc:SdkSinglePageViewer
  Name    ="_2689b2c8_b4dc_4b71_b9bd_f95e619122d7"
  Tag     ="mc:ProcessContent Attribute"
  xmlns:cc="clr-namespace:Microsoft.Windows.SdkViewer.Controls;assembly=SdkViewer"
  xmlns   ="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
  <FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>mc:ProcessContent Attribute</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>Specifies which XAML elements should still have content processed by relevant parent elements, even if the immediate parent element may be ignored by a XAML reader due to specifying <Hyperlink NavigateUri="acd9a6ef-b7ca-4146-abb6-60f3b366e9ec.xaml">mc:Ignorable Attribute</Hyperlink>
. The <Run FontWeight="Bold">mc:ProcessContent</Run>
 attribute supports markup compatibility both for custom namespace mapping and for XAML versioning.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Remarks</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>By default, a XAML reader will ignore content within an ignored element. You can specify a specific element by <Run FontWeight="Bold">mc:ProcessContent</Run>
 , and a XAML reader will continue to process the content within the ignored element. This would typically be used if the content is nested within several tags, at least one of which is ignorable and at least one of which is not ignorable.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Multiple prefixes may be specified in the attribute, using a space separator, for example: mc:ProcessContent="ignore:Element1 ignore:Element2".
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Example Attribute Usage</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>
&lt;<Run FontStyle="italic">object</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>xmlns:ignorable<Run FontStyle="italic">="ignorableUri"</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>mc:Ignorable="ignorable"...
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold">mc:ProcessContent</Run>
="ignorable:ThisElementCanBeIgnored"
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>
&lt;ignorable:ThisElementCanBeIgnored>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>...content..., which <Run FontStyle="italic">object</Run>
 would process if ThisElementCanBeIgnored is in fact ignored
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>
&lt;/ignorable:ThisElementCanBeIgnored>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>
&lt;/<Run FontStyle="italic">object</Run>
>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph/>
